Angelo Agrizzi, a former executive at Bosasa will continue with his testimony on Thursday. On Wednesday, Agrizzi told the state capture inquiry that he and CEO Gavin Watson met Myeni at the Sheraton Hotel in Tshwane in 2015. He claimed he was allowed to read the files and take photos. The files contained information about an investigation into alleged tender fraud involving Bosasa. Agrizzi said from 1999 until 2016, when he left Bosasa, the company was involved in corrupt activities, money laundering and tender fraud. 